Fitch Says ‘Whistleblowing’ Short Sellers Increase Volatility

-- B y   V i c t o r i a   B a t c h e l o r
-- 
2011-09-30T02:34:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/fitch-says-whistleblowing-short-sellers-increase-volatility.html
Fitch Ratings said the increased
market volatility and uncertainty introduced by
“whistleblowing” short sellers of Chinese companies is likely
to outweigh any positives for investors from improved corporate
governance and transparency. Fitch commented in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Victoria Batchelor at 
 vbatchelor@bloomberg.net  